be used in `Framefile.json` that can control the color of the frame to be used for framing:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/e6845c4e3b61d50fdbc0ed76c45492b778ae106e/frameit/lib/frameit/editor.rb#L520-L533\r\n\r\nIt can definitely be used this way:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"default\": {\r\n    \"background\": \"./background.jpg\",\r\n    \"keyword\": {\r\n    },\r\n    \"title\": {\r\n      \"text\": \"foo\"\r\n    },\r\n    \"padding\": 0,\r\n    \"frame\": \"WHITE\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"data\": [\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n~~How and if it can be used in `data` I haven't found out / tested yet.~~\r\n\r\nIt was added not so long ago: https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/pull/12824\r\n\r\nIn this PR there is also [a test project that shows](https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/pull/12824#issuecomment-409980860) how this can be used in `data`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"device_frame_version\": \"latest\",\r\n  \"default\": {\r\n  },\r\n\t\"data\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"filter\": \"Red\",\r\n      \"frame\": \"BLACK\"\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"filter\": \"Blue\",\r\n      \"frame\": \"WHITE\"\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"filter\": \"Pink\",\r\n      \"frame\": \"ROSE_GOLD\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```","closed_by":{"login":"joshdholtz","id":401294,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQwMTI5NA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/401294?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz","html_url":"https://github.com/joshdholtz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshdholtz/repos","events_url":"https: